sequenceDiagram
  actor Client
  participant API as WebRtcController
  participant Sessions as WebRtcSessionService
  participant Signaling as WebRtcSignalingService
  participant Auth as WebRtcAuthService
  participant Media as WebRtcMediaService
  participant Bridge as OpenAiRealtimeBridgeService
  participant Provider as OpenAI Realtime API
  participant Conv as ConversationService
  participant Tutor as TutorService
  participant Lesson as LessonService
  participant Usage as UsageService
  participant Context as TeachingContextService
  participant Background as BackgroundAiService
  participant DB as SQLite
  participant Logs as Transcript files

  Client->>API: POST /webrtc/session with optional lesson attribution
  API->>Context: Build compact teaching context when signed in
  Context->>DB: Read lesson, profile, summaries, signals, recent turns
  Context-->>API: Server-only teaching context prompt
  API->>Sessions: assertCapacity and createSession with metadata
  API->>Conv: initializeConversation
  API->>Signaling: buildBootstrapPayload
  API-->>Client: sessionId, conversationId, ICE, persona, voices
  Client->>API: POST /webrtc/session/:id/token
  API->>Auth: createEphemeralToken with persona plus teaching context
  Auth->>Provider: Create realtime session
  Provider-->>Auth: client secret
  API-->>Client: ephemeral token
  Client->>Client: Create lesson-events data channel
  Client->>API: POST /webrtc/session/:id/offer
  API->>Media: handleClientOffer
  Media->>Bridge: ensure peers with teaching-context instructions
  Bridge->>Provider: SDP exchange
  Provider-->>Bridge: SDP answer and realtime events
  Bridge-->>Media: client SDP answer
  API-->>Client: SDP answer
  Client-->>Bridge: WebRTC audio
  Bridge-->>Provider: Realtime audio and data channel events
  Provider-->>Bridge: Synthetic audio and events
  Bridge->>Conv: Record voice turns and token usage
  Client-->>Bridge: lesson-events student_text
  Bridge->>Media: onClientDataMessage
  Media->>Tutor: answerMessage with authenticated metadata
  Tutor->>Lesson: begin turn, decision policy, verifier if applicable
  Tutor->>DB: Persist tutor_turns, usage, evidence as normal
  Media-->>Bridge: tutor_answer event
  Bridge-->>Client: lesson-events tutor_answer
  Client->>API: POST /webrtc/session/:id/close
  API->>Media: closeSession
  API->>Sessions: closeSession
  Sessions->>Conv: finalizeConversation
  Conv->>Logs: Write transcript when available
  API->>Lesson: ensure/reuse lesson and count realtime duration
  Lesson->>DB: Update lesson_sessions
  API->>DB: Insert compact voice-origin tutor_turns row
  API->>Usage: recordRealtimeSession when signed in
  Usage->>DB: Insert ai_usage_ledger session row
  API->>Background: enqueueRealtimeSessionReview when signed in and useful
  Background->>DB: Insert background_ai_jobs realtime_session_review
  API-->>Client: close status, transcript metadata, syncedTurn
